  "algo-league-contest": {
    blocks:     [
          {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Friday, 20 December 2019 – Algo League is the next-generation Coding Contest organised by Avows Technologies in partnership with Digital Native Agenda (DNA23), designed especially to address the needs of a Digital Malaysia."
          },
          {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Meant to enhance awareness of Emergent Tech in Malaysia, Algo League aims to provide a platform for college and university students to demonstrate their analytical and problem-solving skills. This contest also provides students with the opportunity to be recognised by potential employers."
          },
          {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "During the very first iteration of this annual contest, Algo League 1.0 was conducted in two phases on 22 July 2019 (Phase 1 – Multiple Choice Questions) and 25 July 2019 (Phase 2 – Coding). Nearly three hundred (300) students from seven (7) prominent Universities all over Malaysia have participated in this contest presenting a display of talent and innovative thinking."
          },
          {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Phase 1, consisting of 50 multiple choice questions, tested the participants on their technical knowledge, while Phase 2 presented a set of problem statements to the participants, who had to analyse and use appropriate programming language to come up with solutions. The top winners were selected after tallying the combination of points from these two phases."
          },
          {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "We are proud and honoured to declare that three individuals stood out among the ranks of all the ingenious and enterprising young engineers who took part in Algo League 1.0. Low Sheng Rong from Multimedia University was the undisputed champion of Algo League 1.0, winning with a cash prize of RM1500. He was followed by Wong Kai Le from Sunway University and Chuah Seong Rong from Tunku Abdul Rahman University College."
          },
          {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "The prize-giving ceremony was held on 20 December 2019 during Avows Tech-Connect 2020 event, the flagship outreach program of Avows."
          },
          {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Tech-Connect 2020 invited prominent speakers from Microsoft and Averis to share the latest developments in Emergent Technology and how our young people can position themselves to succeed in the arena."
          },
          {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "We wish them the best of luck for the peaks we are sure they will climb in the future."
          }
    ],
  },
  "avows-gbs-awards-2019": {
    description: "Avows won a GBS Pikom award 2019 in Category of Operational Excellence in Information Technology",
    blocks:     [
          {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Avows won a GBS Pikom award 2019 in Category of Operational Excellence in Information Technology (OPEIT). The event was graced by Dato Seri Anwar and esteemed members of Pikom and fellow IT colleagues."
          },
          {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "“I think it’s a representation of how much focus our team has in creating value with customers,” said Ashok K Ramavath. “If we didn’t believe we could truly make a difference for our customers, we wouldn’t have gotten the award.” “Also, we’re ecstatic to share this achievement with our customers around the world. Without them, this wouldn’t be possible.”"
          },
          {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Looking Ahead Creating remarkable experiences isn’t only something our team is devoted to; it’s a value that’s internalised throughout our entire team. Sure, we’re basking in the euphoria of these recognitions but we’re also extremely humbled. We can’t emphasise it enough when we say we owe it all to YOU – this just pushes us to focus even harder on helping you succeed."
          },
          {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "About GBS Awards OM, an initiative of PIKOM introduces the GBS Asia Awards in 2018 (which was previously known as the OM Excellence Awards); where OM expanded the Awards to include regional players and in place with regional benchmarks and moving up the value chain. The Awards initiative were introduced in 2011 by OM as part of the Industry’s endeavour at recognising and rewarding excellence in the Global Business Services and Outsourcing space. The Awards which enters it’s ninth year, is aimed at users and service providers who have individually and collectively pursued global best practises in crafting sustainable value by leveraging on GBS & outsourcing models."
          }
    ],
  },
